<br>
Heck one time I was AFK sitting on top of a wizzy spire prong<br>
(Levitate will let you do that...) waiting for a port up to the nexus. And some twit from pandemonium mana burned me.<br>
<br>
The wizzy spires are often camped by caster PvPers because they know us melee types often use the nexus to ghetto port around.<br>
<br>
So. I guess the best advice on PvP servers is. <br>
<br>
a. Always travel in groups if you can.<br>
b. Keep the MR maxxed.<br>
<br>
Remember on a PvP server its mostly not honorable dueling... it more like ambush/bushwack. A wizzy isn't likely to manaburn someone in a large strong group. Usually they pick off the strays. <br>
<br>
tash is not your friend........<br>
<br>
Oh.. and Remf... the ring war is very hard to do on a PvP server. Imagine you got the ring war started, you are fighting giants and such... and then 20 peeps 55plus show up to start helping the giants and ruining your fun. I've seen this happen (and been on the recieving end of it) a couple of times. Makes accomplishing that quest all the more special because its got that added element to deal with. It is very hard to stealth complete the ring quest because it takes so many people to complete and its obvious what is going to happen based on who is in the GD zone.<br>
<br>
The one time I participated in it and it was successful, basically the uber guild that finished it had a killer team at the EW zone in, a killer team at the Druid Ring, and killer team at the wizzy spire all to keep rival guilds from coming to spoil the fun. Then you need the actual people to do the ring war. I would say on our server only the top 2 or 3 guild can pull this off. Anyone else gets party crashers to their war. Woot.......<br>
<br>
But to get back to the subject at hand... Manaburn needs to be nerfed. Curiously... don't necros have the same sort of skill? Lifeburn? The damage cap for it is limited by the max number of HPs a necro has so I guess its not as nasty.<br>
